        "exhibition.artifacts.crocodile-mummy.period": "Greco-Roman",
        "exhibition.artifacts.crocodile-mummy.desc": "A mummified crocodile honoring the god Sobek.",
        "exhibition.artifacts.roman-emperor-pharaoh.name": "Roman Emperor as Pharaoh",
        "exhibition.artifacts.roman-emperor-pharaoh.period": "Roman Era",
        "exhibition.artifacts.roman-emperor-pharaoh.desc": "A statue depicting a Roman ruler in traditional Egyptian pharaonic dress.",
        "exhibition.halls.grand-hall.name": "Grand Hall (Atrium)",
        "exhibition.halls.grand-hall.era": "New Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.grand-hall.shortDesc": "Stand beneath the towering presence of Ramses II in this colossal architectural masterpiece.",
        "exhibition.halls.grand-hall.longDesc": "The Grand Hall is the majestic entrance to the GEM, dominated by the 82-ton, 11-meter-high statue of King Ramses II. This hall serves as a gateway to the museum’s chronological journey, surrounded by colossal architectural elements from various dynasties.",
        "exhibition.halls.predynastic.name": "Gallery 01: Pre-Dynastic & Early Dynastic",
        "exhibition.halls.predynastic.era": "Old Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.predynastic.shortDesc": "The dawn of civilization. Explore the earliest artifacts that paved the way for the Pharaohs.",
        "exhibition.halls.predynastic.longDesc": "Before the pyramids were built, early Egyptians were already creating exquisite pottery, weapons, and ceremonial palettes. This gallery showcases the foundational era of Egyptian civilization before the unification of the Two Lands.",
        "exhibition.halls.sculpture.name": "Gallery 02: Old Kingdom Sculpture",
        "exhibition.halls.sculpture.era": "Old Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.sculpture.shortDesc": "Marvel at the lifelike masterpieces that immortalized the builders of the pyramids.",
        "exhibition.halls.sculpture.longDesc": "The Old Kingdom is renowned for its breathtaking statuary. This gallery features masterpieces of royal and private sculpture, demonstrating the Egyptians' early mastery over hard stones and their quest for eternal life.",
        "exhibition.halls.old-kingdom-beliefs.name": "Gallery 03: Old Kingdom Beliefs",
        "exhibition.halls.old-kingdom-beliefs.era": "Old Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.old-kingdom-beliefs.shortDesc": "Uncover the religious foundation and early funerary practices of ancient Egypt.",
        "exhibition.halls.old-kingdom-beliefs.longDesc": "Beliefs in the afterlife took physical form during the Old Kingdom. This gallery displays the earliest funerary texts, reserve heads, and magical objects intended to ensure the deceased's survival in the next world.",
        "exhibition.halls.daily-life.name": "Gallery 04: Middle Kingdom Society",
        "exhibition.halls.daily-life.era": "Middle Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.daily-life.shortDesc": "A golden age of literature, arts, and the lives of ordinary citizens.",
        "exhibition.halls.daily-life.longDesc": "The Middle Kingdom is considered the classical age of Egyptian culture. Step into the daily lives of ancient Egyptians through their intricate jewelry, tools, cosmetics, and fascinating recreational games.",
        "exhibition.halls.middle-kingdom-kingship.name": "Gallery 05: Middle Kingdom Kingship",
        "exhibition.halls.middle-kingdom-kingship.era": "Middle Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.middle-kingdom-kingship.shortDesc": "See the humanized, somber faces of the Middle Kingdom Pharaohs.",
        "exhibition.halls.middle-kingdom-kingship.longDesc": "Unlike the divine, idealized statues of the Old Kingdom, Middle Kingdom royal portraits display unprecedented realism. Look into the tired, burdened faces of kings who ruled during an era of profound political change.",
        "exhibition.halls.new-kingdom-society.name": "Gallery 07: New Kingdom Society",
        "exhibition.halls.new-kingdom-society.era": "New Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.new-kingdom-society.shortDesc": "Experience the wealth, cosmopolitan life, and vivid culture of the Empire.",
        "exhibition.halls.new-kingdom-society.longDesc": "During the New Kingdom, Egypt became a global empire. This gallery showcases the unprecedented wealth, luxurious lifestyles, vibrant fashion, and advanced tools used by the society that thrived along the Nile.",
        "exhibition.halls.imperial-kingship.name": "Gallery 08: Imperial Kingship",
        "exhibition.halls.imperial-kingship.era": "New Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.imperial-kingship.shortDesc": "Behold the mighty warrior pharaohs and the revolutionary Amarna period.",
        "exhibition.halls.imperial-kingship.longDesc": "This gallery focuses on the most famous pharaohs in history—from Thutmose III, the Napoleon of Egypt, to the controversial 'heretic king' Akhenaten. Witness the evolution of imperial art and power.",
        "exhibition.halls.afterlife.name": "Gallery 09: Beliefs in the Afterlife",
        "exhibition.halls.afterlife.era": "New Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.afterlife.shortDesc": "Journey through the perilous underworld as ancient Egyptians envisioned it.",
        "exhibition.halls.afterlife.longDesc": "To achieve eternal life, an Egyptian had to pass through the treacherous Duat. Here you will find the magical amulets, intricate sarcophagi, and the Books of the Netherworld designed to protect the soul.",
        "exhibition.halls.tutankhamun.name": "Special: Tutankhamun Galleries",
        "exhibition.halls.tutankhamun.era": "New Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.tutankhamun.shortDesc": "The complete, unedited collection of the boy king’s legendary treasures.",
        "exhibition.halls.tutankhamun.longDesc": "<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2rem;\">For the first time since their discovery in 1922, over 5,000 artifacts from the tomb of King Tutankhamun are displayed together. Experience the gold, the mystery, and the legacy of the boy pharaoh.</p><div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;\"><div class=\"staircase-feature\"><div class=\"feature-icon-wrapper\"><span class=\"material-symbols-outlined\">diamond</span></div><span class=\"feature-text\">The Complete Collection (5,000+ Pieces)</span></div><div class=\"staircase-feature\"><div class=\"feature-icon-wrapper\"><span class=\"material-symbols-outlined\">history_edu</span></div><span class=\"feature-text\">The Legacy of the Boy Pharaoh</span></div></div>",
        "exhibition.halls.royal-mummies.name": "Special: Royal Mummies Hall",
        "exhibition.halls.royal-mummies.era": "New Kingdom",
        "exhibition.halls.royal-mummies.shortDesc": "Stand face-to-face with the legendary rulers of the New Kingdom.",
        "exhibition.halls.royal-mummies.longDesc": "A solemn, respectful environment housing the preserved bodies of Egypt’s greatest pharaohs and queens. Discover the sophisticated mummification techniques that allowed them to survive millennia.",
        "exhibition.halls.grecoroman.name": "Gallery 12: Greco-Roman Period",
        "exhibition.halls.grecoroman.era": "Greco-Roman",
        "exhibition.halls.grecoroman.shortDesc": "The fusion of worlds. Witness the cultural blend of ancient Egypt with Greek and Roman influences.",
        "exhibition.halls.grecoroman.longDesc": "After Alexander the Great’s conquest, Egypt became a crossroads of cultures. This gallery shows the fascinating hybrid art, where Pharaohs were depicted in Greek styles and Roman emperors adopted Egyptian titles.",
        "exhibition.hero_accent": "The Gateway to Eternity",
        "exhibition.hero_title": "Exhibition <br>Halls",
        "exhibition.hero_desc": "Where the echoes of five millennia resonate through glass and stone. Experience the world's largest archaeological treasury.",
        "exhibition.hero_btn": "Begin Journey",
        "exhibition.stair_label": "Vertical History",
        "exhibition.stair_title": "The Grand <span style=\"color: var(--hall-gold);\">Staircase</span>",
        "exhibition.stair_desc": "Ascend through time on a monumental staircase featuring over 87 colossal statues, architectural remnants, and stelae. This vertical gallery tells the story of kingship and the divine in ancient Egypt, leading you to an unparalleled view of the Great Pyramids.",
        "exhibition.stair_feat1": "Royal Statues from the Old Kingdom",
        "exhibition.stair_feat2": "Chronological Ascension (4 Levels)",
        "exhibition.stair_badge": "87+ MONUMENTS",
